cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.NA, cs.AR, cs.SC

Reasoning: 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on improving the speed of SpMV through parallelization on GPU and multi-core architectures.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper proposes different implementations of SpMV for finite fields and rings, which involves designing and analyzing algorithms and data structures.
- cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) is another possible category as SpMV is a common operation in numerical linear algebra and the paper proposes improvements in this area.
- cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) is a less likely category as the paper does not focus on designing new hardware architectures but rather on optimizing existing ones.
- cs.SC (Symbolic Computation) is also a less likely category as the paper does not involve symbolic computation but rather numerical linear algebra.
